{"key":"processedPost-8752118","value":{"id":8752118,"first":8630688,"last":20687613,"when":1218379705,"utime":"08/10/08 05:48 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>antimatt3r said:</b><br />take your verm and put it in the bowl or whatever vessel you are using to mix everything in, then add the water to the verm, mix it up really well and let it sit for 5 minutes or so, letting the verm fully absorb the water, mix it again, then slowly add the flour and mix it all up very very well..... this is what I do anyway, and of course, make sure you measure right.... <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/smile.gif\" alt=\":smile:\" title=\":smile:\"/><br />1/4 cup brf<br />1/4 cup water<br />1/2 cup verm&nbsp;  per 1/2 pint jar <br /></blockquote><br /><br />That's the way to do it.&nbsp; If you get the flour wet, it will clump up and turn to paste.&nbsp; If you mix it slowly with the already moist verm, that doesn't happen.&nbsp; It's how it's demonstrated by Roadkill in <a href=\"http://www.iplayerhd.com/player/eddabfdc-97f8-4201-853a-1203531bb169.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek part 1.</a><br />RR","title":"Re: substrate too wet in jars after sterilization PF TEK, WHY?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}